128→  "title": "Use better-sqlite3 instead of sql.js for local database",
129→  "situation": "Needed a SQLite driver for a Node.js CLI that stores session data locally. Single-user, read-heavy from dashboard, occasional writes during sync.",
130→  "choice": "better-sqlite3 — synchronous C++ binding with native SQLite access, no async overhead.",
131→  "reasoning": "CLI runs locally with no concurrent users. Synchronous API eliminates callback complexity. WAL mode provides concurrent read access for the dashboard while CLI writes.",
132→  "alternatives": [
